g.bouncycastle.oer.its.ieee1609dot2.Opaque$1.run(Unknown Source)\\n```\\n\\nand the report marks coverage using JaCoCo-covered source lines. Because this call site has no line number, the coverage generator cannot associate it with an executed line even when the method is exercised. This is the same issue visible for the other BouncyCastle anonymous dynamic-access classes in the report.\\n\\nI left the focused public-API test in place, but there is no additional test-only change under `src/test/java` that can convert an `Unknown Source` dynamic-access frame into a line-covered call site without changing the upstream library bytecode/debug info or the harness coverage-mapping behavior.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0adc04c4b454168c016a25dffbc93c8190aa2f628d354d38b9\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 764, \"output\": 2902, \"cacheRead\": 61952, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 65618, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1780867004611, \"responseId\": \"resp_0adc04c4b454168c016a25dfbda6748190b2c6fd376d06ef23\"}}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating report generation**\\n\\nI'm looking into dynamic report generation in external attempts because they might not run clean. There’s a stale report that doesn’t reflect new tests correctly. The prompt says attempts are newly none, which raises my suspicion. If they ran the report post-test, the Jacoco method coverage should cover Opaque$1, but the report shows null. I think it would be best to keep the test as is, but I might add a minor update: `assertThat(decodedValue).isNotNull();`.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0adc04c4b454168c016a25dfbe6b4c8190b1772995e9e0f33f\\\",\\\"typ