ect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\\\n\\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4010:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Append issue context and concrete chunk limits for oversized dynamic-access runs.\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4015:    (§WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report).\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4049:            pipeline_argv.append(\\\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\\\")\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4834:    (§WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report).\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:5090:    (§WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking, §GIT-issue-linking).\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:6739:        \\\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\\\",\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:6742:            \\\"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \\\"\\nforge/forge_metadata.py:6743:            \\\"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\\\"\\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_improve_coverage.py:141:This PR improves dynamic-access coverage for {coordinates} by generating additional tests.\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:95:- Script results are written in `output/results.json` (§WF-dynamic-access-workflow, §WF-forge-workflow-drivers).\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:101:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access] \\\\\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:126:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:386:coordinates, active dynamic-access classes, source-context paths, and Gradle\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:421:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:452:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:459:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:482:see `docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md`.\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:62:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:81:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:100:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:119:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:139:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:158:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:177:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:196:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:215:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:234:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:254:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:274:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:294:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:314:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:335:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:356:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:376:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:391:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Composite strategy: runs javac_iterative to fix compilation, then improves dynamic-access coverage.\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:398:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:420:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:441:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:442:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:475:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Composite strategy: runs java_run_iterative to fix runtime failures, then improves dynamic-access coverage.\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:482:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:533:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Pi bulk dynamic-access strategy. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, which iterates through uncovered classes and refines coverage class by class, this strategy gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one prompt and asks it to cover the missing accesses in a single broad pass.\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:538:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:552:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Codex bulk dynamic-access strategy. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, which iterates through uncovered classes and refines coverage class by class, this strategy gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one prompt and asks it to cover the missing accesses in a single broad pass.\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:557:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:571:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Pi graphify-assisted bulk dynamic-access strategy. It first builds graphify context from downloaded source artifacts, then gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one broad pass. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, it does not run the class-by-class refinement loop.\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:576:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:591:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Codex graphify-assisted bulk dynamic-access strategy. It first builds graphify context from downloaded source artifacts, then gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one broad pass. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, it does not run the class-by-class refinement loop.\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:596:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:617:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:618:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:640:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:641:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:663:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:664:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:686:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:687:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:726:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:745:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:759:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Library-update strategy: skips primary workflow, directly runs dynamic-access coverage improvement on existing tests.\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:764:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:779:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Library-update bulk dynamic-access strategy: runs only the optimistic full-report workflow against existing tests, without per-class refinement.\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:784:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration-update.md\\\"\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:799:    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Library-update composite strategy: bulk dynamic-access coverage in one broad pass first, then per-class iterative refinement of any stragglers. Mirrors the iterative library-update strategy but starts with a faster bulk pass.\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:805:      \\\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration-update.md\\\",\\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:806:      \\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\": \\\"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\\\"\\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:762:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Return fully covered dynamic-access categories that became uncovered.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:795:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Fail PR publication if old/new stats show a dynamic-access category regression.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:814:    \\\"\\\"\\\"Format a single dynamic-access stats entry.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:823:    \\\"