olResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_vV0mmveErguKUIzD7kty8zNZ|fc_0fdae1f3b7cf2e3e016a25dc476c208197aee8445980c00ac0\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"metadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15on/1.70/reachability-metadata.json\\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk18on/1.77/reachability-metadata.json\\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcutil-jdk18on/1.77/reachability-metadata.json\\nmetadata/org.bouncycastle/bcpkix-jdk15to18/1.77/reachability-metadata.json\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1780866119964}]}\n../1504-01be332b/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk18on:1.77/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-07T20-51-47-597822Z.log:2729:[thinking] I need to ensure there are no failing tests. The OEROptional is using UINT8, which causes it to fail natively. Since I'm currently working with the test class, OEROptional still has its issues. Should I remove or disable it? It seems the OEROptional test is untracked and inactive. However, since the task specifies focusing on the active class, it might be better not to broaden the scope unnecessarily. Yet, leaving it failing isn’t ideal either. The current task wants active coverage, so I'm still figuring out the best approach.\n../1504-01be332b/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk18on:1.77/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-07T20-51-47-597822Z.log:2733:[thinking] If OEROptional continues to fail, even though ItsUtils is covered, it won't be accepted. I could edit OEROptional to fix the native failure, but that shifts focus to another dynamic-access class. The developer suggests maintaining coverage for each dynamic-access test file, but I need to keep in mind that the user requested to focus only on the active class. Failing tests are important to address since external verification will fail. It appears OEROptional uses UINT8, leading to missing metadata issues.\n../1504-01be332b/human-intervention-logs/org.bouncycastle:bcutil-jdk18on:1.77/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-06-07T20-51-47-597822Z.log:2739:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Analyzing test failures**\\n\\nI need to ensure there are no failing tests. The OEROptional is using UINT8, which causes it to fail natively. Since I'm currently working with the test class, OEROptional still has its issues. Should I remove or disable it? It seems the OEROptional test is untracked and inactive. However, since the task specifies focusing on the active class, it might be better not to broaden the scope unnecessarily. Yet, leaving it failing isn’t ideal either. The current task wants active coverage, so I'm still figuring out the best approach.\\n\\n**Considering OEROptional failures**\\n\\nIf OEROptional continues to fail, even though ItsUtils is covered, it won't be accepted. I could edit OEROptional to fix the native failure, but that shifts focus to another dynamic-access class. The developer suggests maintaining coverage for each dynamic-access test file, but I need to keep in mind that the user requested to focus only on the active class. Failing tests are important to address since external verification will fail. It appears OEROptional uses UINT8, leading to missing metadata issues.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0fdae1f3b7cf2e3e016a25dc776e28819790485ac53b9ba7e3\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"content\\\":[],\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqJdykzX2qJ32PnY1KwCKgpYWiMI87QuC1ApZ0SgQmJ51SsRCVsRncbfPgYh3eeVKYX93Von_ofW04N70o7Z49kpjbr8Rmx1l-PjBP9qiEEImidrchkG0aCcQZlBlbgyJLoM8ZsboLkuaUEkNa6Ol55pP75Ae5r4PzX1D0Ww4kh4NYqhocpafAMonoiKzGg2UjQ5nSViXjYBTJ_215ujfNCXQyJ0TTvA8TlvidWK94iu8xodCLnIdq5oLrq9MvwdIquA3PEIA11rYEX6m4o2FBK0lW6DVLCR99KJomAZxgkWavZk0DlqRVUhmDr3KGsypD63B2WGeK0bsXYhjigeYEjalKC7--rs5UPn0XFJoLEI4uRmwMClt6OvFcJTqxr3x86W7f_5UiLMfGPf4nKOff4VJ4lfnoZEunFIMBh045bD4r6wKdts-gHC6UD1vw-2Ovxd7y